New Alaska Airlines Jet Service Between
Anchorage & Dutch Harbor Begins April 17
• Along with our travel partners PenAir and Reeve Aleutian
Airways, we offer great connections between Seattle and
Dutch Harbor.
Russian Far East Service Resumes June 6
• Alaska Airlines initiates service to the Russian Far East cities of
Magadan and Khabarovsk on June 6. Our ground-breaking new
service to the Pacific seaport city of Vladivostok begins June 8.
• Four weekly flights are offered to the Far East with convenient
connections from the West Coast.
• Russian Far East Vacations range from 6 to 15 days. For more
information contact your travel agent or Alaska Airlines
Vacations at 1-800-468-2248.
Frequent Flights Offered Between The
Pacific Northwest & California Every Business Day
• 27 nonstops between Seattle and the Bay Area
• 41 flights between Seattle and the Los Angeles Area
• 19 nonstops between Portland and the Bay Area
• 29 flights between Portland and the Los Angeles Area
